<p>就在这一消息发布几天前，中国电子公司华为发布了配备国产芯片的新款智能手机<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2023-09-04/look-inside-huawei-mate-60-pro-phone-powered-by-made-in-china-chip?srnd=premium&amp;sref=10lNAhZ9&amp;leadSource=uverify%20wall">Mate 60 Pro</a> 。根据分析公司 TechInsights 的一份报告，华为与芯片制造商中芯国际合作开发了一款新的 Kirin 9000s 芯片。中芯国际的高水平 7 纳米技术似乎为 Mate 60 Pro 提供了超越典型 5G 手机的下载速度。</p><p>整个Mate 60 Pro的发布以及随后的实力证明与<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/us-netherlands-and-japan-reportedly-agree-to-limit-chinas-access-to-chipmaking-equipment-174204303.html">美国、日本和荷兰限制中国芯片准入</a>和限制其生产能力的努力形成了鲜明对比。就在八月，拜登总统签署了一项<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/biden-signs-executive-order-restricting-investment-in-chinese-tech-companies-230728855.html">行政命令，进一步限制对从事半导体等技术的中国企业的投资</a>。此前的限制专门针对华为，包括一月份<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/us-government-cracks-down-exports-tech-huawei-125040916.html">禁止向这家中国公司出口美国技术的许可证</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/china-plans-40-billion-fund-for-its-chip-industry-112119881.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/china-plans-40-billion-fund-for-its-chip-industry-112119881.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 70e2c791-b977-4f5a-b163-eacddee160df</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 05 Sep 2023 11:21:19 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693925978</ingested><modified> 2023-09-05T14:59:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="3117" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2019-11/b